[thinking] I'm looking at why existing serialization tests fail natively on the Object constructor before reaching the readObject call. It seems tricky to figure out how to avoid this native failure. Since we’re not supposed to edit metadata, I wonder if accessing the readObject under native requires Object constructor metadata. Maybe if the class has serialization metadata generated by the agent, it could help? Also, the external Forge merges metadata from the agent to native, yet no edits to metadata are allowed.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Investigating JaCoCo Instrumentation**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm looking into whether JaCoCo can instrument bcprov classes since they might be loaded from a dependency. The dynamic access report utilizes the JaCoCo execution data, and if a method is executed, it should mark the call as covered. If the report shows false coverage, I’m wondering if this indicates they weren't instrumented. Could it also be due to tests added after the report generation? The build or report might be stale, and I need to check the timestamps.
[thinking] 
